{"lemma":"صِفَةٍ","slug":"صِفَةٍ","root":"#.ص.ف","root_slug":"_-ص-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ص-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24407","n44608"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of وَصَفَ (waṣafa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"quality, feature, characteristic"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"adjective (morphological category)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a word or phrase that modifies a noun"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attribute","tags":["attributive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bench, stone bench"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sofa, sill, shelf, console"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vestibule, anteroom, entrance-room, portico, an elevated room over or before an edifice including a mosque and even over a sepulchre","examples":[{"text":"أَهْلُ الصُّفَّةِ","english":"the companions of the prophet Mohammed"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seat of a saddle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a small part, a little of"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a short while, a trice"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare وَصَفَ (waṣafa, “to describe, to characterize”).\n\nFrom Aramaic צִפָּא / צִיפָּא (ṣippā), צִפְּתָא / צִיפְּתָא (sippəṯā) / ܨܝܦܬܐ / ܨܶܦ݁ܬ݂ܳܐ (ṣeppəṯā, “mat”), suspected to be from Akkadian 𒍦𒉺𒀀𒌅 (ṣip-pa-a-tu /⁠ṣippatu⁠/, “a type of reed”), or instead סִפָּא / סִיפָּא (sippā) / ܣܷܦܴ݁ܐ (seppā, “threshold, doorpost”), alleged to be from Akkadian 𒈨𒁍 (sip-pu /⁠sippu⁠/, “doorsill”) but possibly cognate to it."},"ipa":["/sˤi.fa/","/sˤuf.fa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24407","headword_ar":"صُفَّةٌ","root":"Sf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An appertenance of a house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, [in none of which is it explained,]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a building, like a wide"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahuw","text_ar":"بَهُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here used in a postclassical sense, as meaning a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of vestibule,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portico, for shade and shelter, open in front"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a long roof"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceiling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tur~ap","text_ar":"طُرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a building [app. meaning what is above described]; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiyfapN","text_ar":"سَقِيفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S and Msb and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sqf","text_ar":"سقف"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiyfapN","text_ar":"سَفِيفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~apN","text_ar":"سُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zul~apN","text_ar":"ظُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a roof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covering, for shade and shelter, over the door of a house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from a house to another house opposite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~apN","text_ar":"سُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiyfapN","text_ar":"سَقِيفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) [for the meaning assigned to it by Golius as from the S, and by Freytag as from the K and S, (“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scamnum discubitorium,"},{"kind":"text","text":"fere"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ex lapidibus structum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"”) I find no authority in any Arabic work: in Egypt, it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shelf of marble"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of common stone, about four"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1694},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feet high, supported by two"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more arches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a single arch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"figured and described in the Introduction to my work on the Modern Egyptians; this being app. so called because resembling in form, though not in size, a porch:] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufafN","text_ar":"صُفَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifaAfN","text_ar":"صِفَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suf~aAtN","text_ar":"صُفَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu AlS~uf~api","text_ar":"اَهْلُ الصُّفَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suf~ap","text_ar":"صُفَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] was an appellation applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain persons who were the guests of El-Islám,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported by the charity of the Muslims,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of poor refugees, and houseless men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who passed the night in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suf~ap","text_ar":"صُفَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mosque of the Prophet"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in El-Medeeneh"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which was a covered place, an appertenance of the mosque,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roofed over with palm-sticks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 379; [where see more;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thither they resorted for lodging; and sometimes they were few, and sometimes they were many:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[SM says,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have drawn up a list of their names, in a tract, to the number of ninety-two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ninetythree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awofaADN","text_ar":"اَوْفَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [ISd says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAbu yawomi","text_ar":"عَذَابُ يَوْمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uf~api","text_ar":"الصُّفَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The punishment of the day of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suf~ap","text_ar":"صُفَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAbu yawomi AlZ~ul~api","text_ar":"عَذَابُ يَوْمِ الظُّلَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned in the Kur xxvi. 189]: (M, TA:) Lth says that the former was"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a day on which a certain people disobeyed their apostle, wherefore God sent upon them heat and clouds which overspread them, so that they perished:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and Az says that it is not the same as that mentioned in the Kur, and that he knew not what is meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*Ab ywm AlSf~p","text_ar":"عذاب يوم الصفّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, (TA:) it seems, however, that both mean the same, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uf~apu","text_ar":"الصُّفَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ul~apu","text_ar":"الظُّلَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are one in meaning. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An appertenance of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saroj","text_ar":"سَرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horse's saddle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, M, IAth, Mgh, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyvarap","text_ar":"مِيثَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wvr","text_ar":"وثر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel's saddle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (IAth, L, TA; *) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing with which it is covered, between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qarabuwsaAni","text_ar":"قَرَبُوسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are its fore part and its hinder part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or, (M, TA,) as also of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing that comprises within it"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taDum~u","text_ar":"تَضُمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two pieces of wood called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroquwataAni","text_ar":"عَرْقُوَتَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two pads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffed things, called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidaAdaAni","text_ar":"بِدَادَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above them and beneath them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufafN","text_ar":"صُفَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifaAfN","text_ar":"صِفَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter mentioned by Sb. (M.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long period"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnN","text_ar":"زَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of time. (O, K, TA.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$onaA Suf~apN mina Ald~ahori","text_ar":"عِشْنَا صُفَّةٌ مِنَ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We lived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have lived, a long period of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity of grain that is put upon the palm of the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in a trad. of Abu-d-Dardà, in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaHotu laA A^amolku","text_ar":"اَصْبَحْتُ لَا اَمْلكُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suf~apF walaA luf~apF","text_ar":"صُفَّةً وَلَا لُفَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I became so that I possessed not the quantity of grain that might be put on the palm of the hand, nor a morsel of food"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~uf~apu","text_ar":"اللُّفَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~uqomapu","text_ar":"اللُّقْمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","O","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n44608","headword_ar":"صِفَةٌ","root":"wSf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quality; an attribute; a property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a description,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aggregate of the qualities or attributes or properties"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing. So explained voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinofN","text_ar":"صِنْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwrapN","text_ar":"صُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See its syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifapN","text_ar":"صِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in grammar,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEotN","text_ar":"نَعْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An epithet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A word denoting an attribute"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonFY","text_ar":"مَعْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAt","text_ar":"ذَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"). Under this term are comprised the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asm fAEl","text_ar":"اسم فاعل"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asm mfEwl","text_ar":"اسم مفعول"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sfp m$b~hp","text_ar":"صفة مشبّهة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfEl AltfDyl","text_ar":"افعل التفضيل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (I'Ak, sect."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlSfp","text_ar":"الصفة"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alm$b~hp bAsm AlfAEl","text_ar":"المشبّهة باسم الفاعل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiqapN mu$ab~ahapN","text_ar":"صِقَةٌ مُشَبَّهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A simple epithet"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an epithet resembling an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asm fAEl","text_ar":"اسم فاعل"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifapN gaAlibapN","text_ar":"صِفَةٌ غَالِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An epithet in which the substantive character predominates."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifapN","text_ar":"صِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a general term for an attributive word, is also applied by Lth and other old writers to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An adverbial n. of place or time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a preposition."},{"kind":"text","text":"It is so applied in the L and TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Enl","text_ar":"عنل"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c. It was applied to the former by Fr, (T, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZarofN","text_ar":"ظَرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and to the latter also. (L, TA, ubi supra.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}